snippet.textDisplay:
it's so relatable. I had 4 teachers now.
A guy that was super cool and knew some nice tricks to do in everyday life. I knew him and I could have a nice conversation with him without being awkward. There was then a boring girl, I hated being with her for hours. I tried to talk with her but she would just cut me off and stop talking to me. When she tried to actually teach me, it was garbage that I wouldn't understand. She was basically doing it on the side and really didn't seem to enjoy the job. There was another instructor. He showed me the tricks the girl failed to show me (parallel and 90-degree backward parking) He brought me downtown and told me to turn on a OneWay (i didn't) that was stressful but I learned my lesson. I laughed it off. Next was a Mexican guy, he had an accent that was in the way sometimes, or he just talked really fast and I couldn't process any of it. He was a stressful and pushy dude, I'm not taking a class with him again because of that. I wanted to cry at the end of my evaluation with him. It's supposed to be fun FFS. My next teacher is older so I hope he's going to be like the third one.
